snippet.textDisplay:
4:37

Air pressure from above is the same as air pressure from below

Realize air pressure pushes all directions

Feel the air against your body snuggling up to each other as they push against you

Move, and they scatter. Don't move and they scatter. Don't move and you're still moving.

But there's always more of them

Snuggling up to each other as they push against you from seemingly everywhere all at once

Did I mention they were gaseous? They move fast. Constantly and in all directions. But if you zoom in as time slows way down, at any given snapshot of the surface of your skin they snuggle in and collectively push outward against you lined up, nestled in tight.
